  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  First time sudden cardiac arrest with ICD implantation during hospitalization, over
             age 21 years, working telephone in the home, deliverable address for 1 year

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Receiving an ICD for primary prevention of sudden cardiac arrest, inability to read,
             speak, or understand English, no telephone at home or no current address, cognitive or
             physical impairments that prohibited ability to give informed consent.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
